I was sneezing non stop; injection site was sore; can't taste; nose started running/ my nose was like a faucet, non stop, clear; asked if it can it give her COVID since her symptoms were similar to COVID; asked if it can it give her COVID since her symptoms were similar to COVID; I felt scratchy in my throat; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). This consumer reported similar events for two patients. This is the first of two reports. A 70-year-old female patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, lot number: EL3248 and expiration date not provided), via an unspecified route of administration in the left arm on 13Jan2021 at a single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The patient's medical history was not reported. There were no concomitant medications. The patient previously took shingles vaccine for immunization and experienced shingles. The patient reported that she got her first dose of the COVID vaccine on 13Jan2021. On 17Jan2021 night and into 18Jan2021, she felt scratchy in her throat. She did not think anything of it because the temperature change was not unusual in the patient's state and so she thought it was that. But, on 19Jan2021, her throat was more scratchy and then her nose started running more. By Wednesday, 20Jan2021, her nose was like a faucet, non stop, clear and her throat was definitely scratchy and she was sneezing non stop. Her injection site was sore too which she totally expected. Now, her physician has given her a steroid pack and did a rapid test, which was negative but the following day they are doing a PCR test, so, she will see. She also stated that she can still smell but can't taste and that started last night, 20Jan2021. She asked if they were seeing these. And if this was listed or being reported and if she should get the second dose. She went on to state that "I would not call my symptoms severe and I'm having my PCR tomorrow, but when they mention to me that they have had other patients with this experience". She also asked if it can it give her COVID since her symptoms were similar to COVID and other people are having symptoms. She also reported that 4 months ago, she got her first shingles vaccination and "it knocked me on my butt, I still haven't got the second injection but I got shingles" and asked should she have gotten the COVID vaccine if she just got over shingles 3-4 weeks ago. She reported that she got her first dose of the COVID vaccine on 13Jan2021 and her second dose is scheduled for 30Jan2021 (17days apart). She did not have a question about the timing of the vaccine, only mentioned when her second dose was due and the it was 17 days after the first. She wanted to know if Pfizer was seeing a lot of this, and it could this her body reacting to the vaccine. She wanted to know what she should do with the second vaccine, if she should get it. She works at a school and has been making sure to wash her hands and everything. The outcome of the events Rhinorrhoea, and Vaccination site pain was unknown. The outcome of the event ageusia was not recovered while the outcome of the rest of the events was recovering.; Sender's Comments: Linked Report(s) : US-PFIZER INC-2021082498 same drug/event, different patients

Received Pfizer COVID vaccine on Wed night 1/31/21 at 5:50pm. I had no prior recent illnesses prior to getting the shot. About 24 hours later, developed fevers/chills, body aches, headaches, and fatigue, and a notable pain in the front of neck -- felt like tender thyroid. Temp was 100.3F on Thursday night 1/14. Took ibuprofen and went to bed. Next day felt fine, went to work, but symptoms returned on Friday night without fever. Symptoms persisted through the weekend without fever until Sunday AM 1/17/21 at 3:40am, I woke up with a temp of 101.7F. Went to get tested for COVID on Sunday 1/17/21 and Tuesday 1/19/21. Both times were negative (both rapid and PCR). Remained febrile on Monday and Tuesday AM. Went to urgent care on Monday 1/18/21 and was negative for flu, but provider observed the thyroid was tender. TSH was checked on 1/18/21 and was abnormal, 0.027 and FT4 was 3.20. Had virtual appt with PCP on 1/19/21, and she ordered more blood tests to evaluate the hyperthyroidism. On 1/21, repeat TSH was 0.014, and FT4 and T3 were both high. Inflammatory markers were elevated, liver function tests were mildly elevated, but thyroid antibodies were all negative. Over the course of the week after getting the shot, I experienced tachycardia, palpitations, fatigue, and shortness of breath and dyspnea on exertion with simple tasks like walking up a flight of stairs or getting up from the couch to walk to the kitchen. PCP ordered an echocardiogram to evaluate the dyspnea on exertion, but it was normal. I had radioactive iodine uptake thyroid scan performed on 2/3 and 2/4, and it was notable for markedly low 24-hour uptake, consistent with Hashimoto's thyroiditis, or other types of thyroiditis. As of 2/5/21, I am feeling significantly better from the past 3 weeks, and the hyperthyroid symptoms have improved and flu-like symptoms have resolved. Due to possible relation to the vaccine, I have delayed the 21-day booster shot to 23 days, and plan to get it this afternoon 2/5/21.
LAB_DATA: 1/18/21 - TSH 0.027; FT4 3.20 1/21/21 - TSH 0.014; FT4 4.85; T3 12.1; anti-TPO 17; alk ph 135; ALT 54; ESR 79; CRP 46; TSI < 10  Echocardiogram 1/27/21: Normal LV size and systolic function; Normal RV size and function; no significant valvular abnormalities, no pericardial effusion  Radioactive iodine thyroid uptake scan: Markedly decreased 24 hour radioiodine uptake, consistent with Hashimoto's or other types of thyroiditis. Correlate with clinical course.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Rosacea; Postherpetic Neuralgia; Shingles; Information has been received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation and referred to a female patient of unknown age. No information was provided regarding medical history, concurrent conditions, or concomitant medications. On or around 28-JAN-2015, the patient was vaccinated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster) (strength, dose, route, lot# and expiration date were not reported). Shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered a rash in her face and redness and pain in her forehead area. The patient was diagnosed with shingles, rosacea and postherpetic neuralgia. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the product. The patient also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of her condition. As a result of the manufacturer, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the events shingles, rosacea and postherpetic neuralgia was considered as not recovered. The events were considered related to zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX).   The lawyer considered the events shingles, rosacea and postherpetic neuralgia to be disability.

Cough, sputum production, with sometimes streaks of blood, rhinorrhea, facial pressure and myalgias; This initial spontaneous report was received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation and refers to a patient of unknown age and gender. No information was provided regarding concomitant medications, concurrent conditions or medical history. On or around 04-NOV-2015, the patient was inoculated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) for routine adult health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (dose, dose number, route, anatomical site of vaccination, lot # and expiration date were not provided). On an unknown date (reported as shortly after receiving the vaccine), the patient suffered cough, sputum production, with sometimes streaks of blood, rhinorrhea, facial pressure and myalgias. The patient was diagnosed with pneumonia. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the vaccine. The patient also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of the patient condition. In addition, the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, the patient had suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. Finally, as direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of pneumonia was not recovered. The causal relationship between the event and zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) was assessed as related.  Pneumonia was considered a disabling event by the reporter.  Upon internal review, pneumonia was considered a medically significant event.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Injection site soreness; Difficulty lifting arm; Arm heaviness; Muscle aches; Influenza-like symptoms; only the adjuvant was administered without the antigen; only the adjuvant was administered without the antigen; feeling tired; Sniffles; Gastrointestinal symptoms; Altered digestion; Increased urination; This case was reported by a consumer  and described the occurrence of injection site pain in a 64-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   Concomitant products included pneumococcal vaccine (Pneumonia Vaccine).   In November 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). In November 2020, less than a day after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced injection site pain, mobility decreased, heaviness in arm, tiredness, sniffles, gastrointestinal symptom nos, digestion impaired, urinary frequency, muscle pain, influenza-like symptoms, inappropriate preparation of medication and inappropriate dose of vaccine administered. Shingrix was interrupted. On an unknown date, the outcome of the injection site pain, mobility decreased, tiredness, sniffles, gastrointestinal symptom nos, urinary frequency, muscle pain and influenza-like symptoms were recovered/resolved and the outcome of the heaviness in arm, digestion impaired, inappropriate preparation of medication and inappropriate dose of vaccine administered were unknown. Additional details were provided as follows: The age at vaccination was not reported. Patient received the pneumonia vaccine one month earlier to Shingrix. It was reported that patient received the Shingrix with only adjuvant part and experienced symptoms including injection site soreness, difficulty lifting arm due to heaviness, muscle ache and flu-like symptoms. 24 Hours after the vaccination patient felt tired with mild sniffles, gastrointestinal symptoms including altered digestion, and increased urination. As patient received the Shingrix without antigen,which led to iappropriate preparation of medication and inappropriate dose of vaccine administered. It was reported that the symptoms lasted approximately 1-2 days. The blood test was performed for antibody levels which demonstrated antibodies to shingles. Patient was unwilling to be re-vaccinated with properly reconstituted Shingrix vaccine due to having side effects from adjuvant.

1/28- Moderna vaccine to left deltoid approximately 1000 AM. Felt fine the rest of the day. Very tired in the evening and went to sleep early. Took PM medications- Xyzal 1 tab PO HS, Xanax 0.5 mg PO HS. 1/29-Woke to Left arm was sore, felt like I had received TDap injection, like I was punched in the arm- localized to Deltoid.  Took AM medications as normal- Wellbutrin XL 150 mg QD, Effexor 75 mg QD, B12 SL, Multivitamins QD As the day progressed, left arm soreness and discomfort became more pronounced and then went from localized to circumferential to left arm. Also noted discomfort and soreness to left axilla and soreness to left lateral/posterior cervical neck area. Became increasingly tired, weak, left arm was weaker than right arm with grip.  Headache was pounding and predominantly bilateral temporally.  Decreased appetite. Non productive cough.  Mid day, started to have freezing bilateral upper and lower extremities. Applied wool socks and clothing layers to accommodate. Temperature to forehead was 99.0, Right ear 101.4 and Left ear 102.0. Pulse ox 97% on room air. Took 1 gram APAP prophylactically, also took Zicam SL. Tolerated as much PO fluids as possible, water.  Increased flu like signs and symptoms for the rest of the day, no actual fever recorded. Literally had on thermals, top and bottoms. 2 pair of wool socks, gloves, and a hoodie. Wrapped in bed with 2 blankets.  Through the night, had discarded all clothing and remained in shirt and had sheet covering. Difficult night sleeping with the soreness to left arm and left axilla, was not able to get comfortable.  1/30- Woke, still, felt signs and symptoms of flu, body aches, pains, weak, tired, and decreased appetite.  A noticeable audible wheeze, shortness of breath with minimal exertion, and persistent dry cough. Cough remained non-productive.  All other signs and symptoms from the day before remained and the soreness to the left upper arm, left axilla, and left neck. Flu like signs and symptoms were just as intense as day before. Chills were consistently inconsistent with start and end, noticeable bilateral hands and feet were freezing. Afebrile, pulse ox 97% room air . Continued to treat prophylactically with APAP and Zicam, po fluids, rest.  1/31- Difficult night sleeping again related to discomfort to left side of upper torso. Felt a little better concerning weakness and being tired. Headache subsided some from it?s intensity. Started to have stomach discomfort, diarrhea, and remained short of breath with minimal exertion. Felt as if I was not able to expand my lungs to their full capacity, thus yawned a lot and had to continue to try to expand lungs. Continued to have flu signs and symptoms (not as intense as past 2 days), diarrhea STARTED, and feeling tired continued. Shortness of breath decreased in severity and lungs continued to feel a decline in expansion with inhalation. Continued to treat prophylactically and rest. Pulse ox 99% room air. Afebrile. 2/1- Difficult night sleeping related to left upper torso soreness and discomfort. Diarrhea continued into this day. No nausea. Tolerating PO fluids; however, feeling weak and tired.  Left upper arm soreness and discomfort less than initial onset. Left axilla remained sore and left side of neck. Pulse ox 99% room air. Afebrile. 2/2- Diarrhea subsided, flu signs and symptoms continued to decrease in initial intensity. Shortness of breath not as extreme; however, continued to feel as if not able to expand lungs to full capacity. Left upper arm soreness and discomfort almost resolved, left axilla beginning to decrease in soreness along with left side of neck. Only prominent s/s is feeling tired and inability to expand lungs to full capacity. Pulse ox 99% room air. Afebrile. 2/3- Feeling 95% better, closer to baseline. Worst days were the first 2 after the injection; however, still remain unable to expand lung capacity to full expansion with inhaling, thus requiring multiple attempts and yawning. Pulse ox 99% room air. Afebrile 2/4- 99% to baseline and feeling better, continue to have decreased expansion of lung capacity. Pulse ox 99% room air. Afebrile
OTHER_MEDS: Wellbutrin XL 150 mg PO QD, Effexor ER 75 mg PO QD, Xanax 0.5 mg PO HS/PRN Sleep, Xyzal 1 tab HS, Multivitamin, zicam SL PRN, B12 SL PRN

Anaphylactic reaction; A spontaneous report (United States) was received from a consumer who is a female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced an anaphylactic reaction.  The patient's medical history included allergy to azithromycin (hives). Concomitant medications were not reported.  On 09 JAN 2021, the patient received her first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unknown) for the prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 09 JAN 2021, while sitting in the waiting area, 8 to 10 minutes after the injection, the patient experienced warm feeling, tongue getting bigger and collapsed. She was given intravenous medications and health care professionals were monitoring her vitals. The patient was transported to emergency via ambulance and was given two doses of EpiPen in the ambulance and by the time she arrived hospital she was doing better and was discharged after 4 hours.  Treatment provided included EpiPen and intravenous medications.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported.  The outcome of event anaphylactic reaction was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a female patient of unknown age with relevant medical history of allergy to azithromycin who  received her first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unknown) for the prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection and experienced a serious medically significant unlisted event of an anaphylactic reaction within 8-10 minutes after the injection. The reaction was described as warm feeling, tongue getting bigger and collapsed. Patient was transported to ER and given two doses of EpiPen while in the ambulance.  By the time she arrived at the hospital, she was doing better and was discharged after 4 hours. Treatment also included IV medications. Based on temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event within 8-10 minutes after the vaccine administration, a causal relationship cannot be excluded and the event of anaphylaxis reaction is possibly related.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Later that night after the vaccination I woke up hot, my body was achy all over, I had a headache and begin to cough.  I took another dose of cough meds but it didnt work.  That next morning I visited my PCP and my temp was 98.7 when I arrived but the temp elevated to 99.9 while there and another temp was taken shortly after and was 100.8 so I was advised to go back home.  Once home I was so tired and weak I could barely make it to the couch.  My temp  then was 101 so I laid down.  The couch was so bad it caused my throat to begin to hurt.  I lost my taste and sense smell, my body ached so bad it was unbareable and I developed various bruises all over my body still while continue to cough presistantly.  I was off work for about 3 days and those 3 days were the worse days of my life, I was so unconfortable and scared it was almost unbareable I thought I was going to die. And on Thursday the symptoms begin to diminish and by that night it was if nothing had ever happened.
CUR_ILL: nothing besides the AE to the 1st vaccination

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Painless Left supraclavicular lymph note about 1.5-2 cm, painless.  No other symptoms, due to my age and no other lymph nodes and that it persisted saw my MD and work up for possibly cancer.
LAB_DATA: Since there were no other symptoms, no other lymph nodes, the supraclavicular node was painless, at the two week point I saw my doctor and work up was started, had normal CBC, LFT, PSA.  CT scan of chest, abdomen and pelvis were negative.   Biopsy performed five weeks after first vaccine, and 1 week after second vaccine was negative  for lymphoma or metastasis.   Of note the node never really changed after the first or second shot it persisted after the first shot, was never painful, maybe a little bigger in AM and smaller in PM.  I and submitting this in case there is a trend, of course at my age I think it was prudent to work it up since there was no change after 2 weeks and this type of lymph node is often an warning sign for abdominal or pelvic cancer.   But in case this is a node that may swell up with the vaccine.

About 3-4 hours after the injection was given, my left arm began to hurt at the sight of the injection. It was sore red and beginning to swell. After a couple more hours it was difficult to even move my arm; it felt as if my tricep was almost entirely immobilized. These symptoms persisted for about three days, with increasingly less intensity, and after the fourth day, I had no adverse symptoms. Exactly six days after receiving the vaccine, the area where the injection was given (tricep) began to feel itchy. When I tried to scratch it, the itch was not relieved but only worsened and began to swell and turn red. By the following day (7 days after injection), the site of injection and area surrounding the site of injection (about 6 inches along my upper and 3-4 inches in width) had swelled up more and was significantly more inflamed than my opposite arm which hadn't changed at all. It had a similar swelling, itch, and pain to the sensation one experiences after getting bitten by a mosquito, but in this case a very very large mosquito bite. By the evening of the seventh day, I began feeling very fatigued both mentally and physically and felt very subtle body aches that usually signal the early signs of a fever (at least for me). Upon feeling feverish symptoms I made a drink of turmeric and ginger root powder with honey and laid down for about an hour in an attempt to rest. After an hour, the body aches and fatigue lessened in intensity but my arm was still swelling and now feeling hot in temperature. The itching was unbearable. I went to go take a warm shower later that night and started to feel a mixture of pressure and pain traveling up my arm and into my chest. I began feeling my lymph nodes on the left side of my breast to find that a lymph node in my armpit and another one on the side of my breast had enlarged to about two inches in diameter. They were painful to the touch and noticeably sore when left untouched. These symptoms persisted with no change for about 2 days. After two days, the swelling and itching in my arm went away but my lymph nodes were still inflamed. They did not reduce in size or in pain until about 7 days after the first signs of these symptoms. After a week all symptoms went away.

Very distinct heartburn feeling; uncomfortable and that lasted about an hour. I had body aches at night time before I went to sleep. The next day I woke up feeling fine. One week later, I had another response. I had my throat start to swell again and this time it was worse. I had itchiness on my arm on the 6th night but I didn't really notice it but that seventh day, I realized there was a rash and itchiness in my arm. I had broken out all over my face - tiny pimples had broken out. I contacted an allergist - I was getting scared about my throat. The allergist said they had seen this a few times after the vaccine - told me to take Pepcid and Benadryl. I did that and that took away the feeling in my throat and made me feel better. I continued both those OT meds for 3 or 4 days. On fourth day, I started getting throat swelling again and the rash on my chest  - these were more mild symptoms than earlier but I called the allergist and he advised I take Pepcid and and Zyrtec instead of Benadryl  for three or four more days. That helped. After that I seemed to be good. On 13th of January - shortness of breath and chest pain. I spoke with Dr and got a COVID test. I had my inhaler at that point (I haven't had asthma in  years and I had to take the inhaler a couple of different times throughout this time). 14th of January - Chest pain. 22nd of January - Chest Monday. On Monday, the 25th, I started taking - in advance of my second dose  of Moderna- Zyrtec  and Pepcid twice a day on the 25th; twice a day on the 26th - on morning of 26th, I took Zyrtec again an hour before the second dose of the Moderna vaccine. I got the 2nd dose on the 26th. (The days that I had chest pain - I took ibuprofen and that seemed to help.)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Rash at injection site

After I received the shot I went to the observation room. I could feel the shot move from my left arm (where I got the shot) to my right arm and down to my hand. After 10 minutes I felt the shot go down both legs at the same time and come back up close to my chest. About 5 minutes after that sensation, my chest got a little tight and I was having a hard time breathing and the right side of my face started to tingle. I looked down at my hands and the finger tips of my right hand were blue.  I raised my hand and the nurse came over and took me to the back room. I thought maybe my hands were dirty, so I washed them off. My right fingertips were still blue.   I could feel tingles all over the right side of my face and my lips went a little numb. I kept pressing them together to see if that would help. My throat started to feel swollen and the nurses gave me some benedryl.  I left after an hour and went home. The tingling on the right side of my face stayed with me for another 2 days.  I have no known allergies.  That was my experience.

As the day progressed the injection site got itchier and itchier and later noted the site was red and hot to the touch, consulted with Employee health over the phone who advised to take a Benadryl since Walk Clinic was closed for the day. Started feeling better after the Benadryl, regarding the itchiness. The rash got bigger though, next morning visited with the Walk in Clinic at the hospital and no tests done but prescribed antibiotics and prescribed prednisone decided not to take it. I took Zyrtec as well.  About 48/72 hours the symptoms started disappearing. On Monday I still had the rash but by Tuesday it was gone.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My mom became very disoriented for 2-3 full days.  She couldn't remember her birthday, where she was, her doctor's name, etc....  We took her to her doctor and she thought she had a stroke.  We went to the ER for every test possible.  She became disoriented and also had to put adult briefs on her.  On Sunday she was driving and on Monday she was totally disoriented.  My dad called and I rushed home 2 1/2 hours away.  This was a terrifying event.   She was glossy eyed and couldn't read.  She didn't have any paralysis; thank goodness.  It was all pretty much mental.
LAB_DATA: MRI, CT Scan, lots of labs, urine, EKG and even a Covid test which was negative.  Her labs and all other tests found nothing.  We were thrown and all they can say was maybe a TIA.  Today, Friday, February 5, 2021, my mom is back to normal.  She can now read, potty, back on her computer, and acts if nothing happened.

On 24 Jan 2021, the patient received their second of two planned doses. On 27 Jan 2021, the patient received a third dose of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 24 Jan 2021, the patient received her second dose of the vaccine and the nurse administering the vaccine missed her deltoid. The patient experienced slight tenderness at the injection site.  On 27 Jan 2021, the patient received a third dose of the vaccine.   On 29 Jan 2021, the patient reported she began experiencing fatigue on an undisclosed date. No treatment information provided.   The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the events; therefore, action taken with the drug in response to the events is not applicable. The outcome of the event, fatigue, was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 37 year old female subject  who experienced non-serious events of nurse missed my deltoid, slight tenderness at the injection site, received a third dose of the vaccine, and fatigue after a second and third dose of mRNA-1273. SYMPTOM_TEXT: irregular hearbeat; Belching; Gas; Stomach cramps; felt antsy; his blood pressure went up the day he hook the vaccine to 200/93; He was anxious feeling; sharp pains in his right eye; Ears Felt Funny; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable consumer (patient). An 80-year-old male patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE; lot number: EK9231; expiry date not reported), via an unspecified route of administration on 19Jan2021 11:00 at single dose for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included high cholesterol and blood pressure abnormal from an unknown date and unknown if ongoing.  Concomitant medication included propranolol hcl for blood pressure and an unspecified cholesterol pill. The patient previously received influenza (Flu shot) on an unspecified date (years) ago for immunization and experienced light headed. The patient reported that his blood pressure went up the day he hook the vaccine to 200/93 and he was real concerned about that. He took a blood pressure pill and was having some sharp pains in his right eye (he had 3-4 at different times). He was anxious feeling and could hear it blowing in his ears (which happens when his blood pressure is high). He stated he has never had his blood pressure that high and has never had any heart problems. The patient asked, whether he was in the danger zone, the danger zone of having a stroke and if they should take their second dose. The patient wondered if they could just take the first dose only. It was further reported that he took the vaccine yesterday or the day before (19Jan2021) at 11'o clock. He didn't have any problems, he just got home. Then 11'o clock at night he had fallen asleep during the day and woke up at that time, 11'o clock and he felt Antsy, his blood pressure was up, his ears puffed real high, he's on Blood Pressure medication. He Clarified further that his First Dose was on 19Jan2021 at 11 o clock during the day. Then 12 hours later that same day, he woke up, and that's when he felt antsy and the blood pressure being up. Normally he takes his Blood Pressure 2-3 times a week but that day it was like 190/80 something. When he saw it, he sat down, and thought if he relaxed it would go down. He went back over in 45 minutes or an hour later and it was 200/93, he thought he had sharp pain in the right eye during that time as well. He Never had that before, he had pain in eye before, but not like this. He then told himself maybe he should take a blood pressure pill, because he was concerned he didn't want to stroke out. He took a Blood pressure pill and then relaxed for an hour later he checked it was 189/82. He waited some more, and it kept coming down. He stayed in the recliner all night. Then on 20Jan2021 he checked and it slipped to 140/55 at about 5 o clock. The Blood pressure kept coming down 10 to 15 points every hour. The last one he took later that day was 118/65. SYMPTOM_TEXT: The patient,  who was a pharmacist, developed fatigue and shortness of breath hours after receiving vaccine.  Two days later, on 01/28/2021, the patient went to local urgent care for worsening shortness of breath and was referred to Hospital for worsening dyspnea and hypoxia.  The patient was admitted to the hospital   We was found to have bilateral pulmonary infiltrates and treated for pneumonia with Rocephin and azithromycin.  He was tested for COVID-19 multiple times, but each of the results were negative.  Despite the negative results, there was high clinical suspicion for COVID-19 and the patient was started on Remdesivir and Decadron.  The  patient's oxygen requirements continued to worsen and the patient was transferred to another facility for higher level of care.  There  his hypoxia worsened and he required mechanical ventilation.  Patient then developed hypotension and required vasopressors for blood pressure support.  Furthermore, patient developed acute renal failure requiring hemodialysis.  Despite mechanical ventilation with FiO2 100%, and for vasopressors, patient clinically deteriorated and family decided to palliatively extubate on 02/05/2021.

The Moderna vaccine administration was painful at the time the shot was received. I experienced symptoms of fatigue and body aches for 24 hours after receiving the vaccine. My left arm was extremely sore and knotted for over a week after administration. The vaccine site was red and splotchy for the first 7 days after getting the shot. By the early morning of the 8th day (01/16/21), the splotches had joined together to make a large red area surrounding the vaccine site, that was raised and hot to the touch. During that entire day, pain was shooting down my left arm to my fingers (particularly the left middle finger) in a manner that felt like how severe arthritis pain is described. The pain became worse as the day went on. I texted a picture of my arm to my boss, who is a physician, to see what he thought I should do. He stated that from the photo, it looked like Cellulitis, and offered to send in an antibiotic to my pharmacy. Soon after, the pain was so intense (especially with movement of the arm) that I had someone drive me to  ER & Urgent Care around 8:30pm. The physician there marked my arm and prescribed 2 antibiotics to begin taking immediately (Bactrim & Amoxicillin) with the instructions to come back in 48 hours. By the next day, the redness was spreading by the hour, which was marked & tracked via photos that documented the progression. By Monday morning, the redness had continued to spread & take up most of my left upper arm. The skin was hot to the touch and swollen. I had my boss look at my arm in the morning and mark the redness, then I had another physician at my office look at it in the afternoon and do the same. Their analysis was that the antibiotics were not working, and I went back to  ER after I got off work at 5pm, which was around the 48-hour mark when I was supposed to return.  ER gave me several IV antibiotics and ordered an Ultrasound of the left arm to make sure there was no blood clot hidden beneath the swelling.  They also took several different lab and blood culture samples. I ended up having a reaction to one of the IV antibiotics (Vancomycin), where they had to counteract the reaction with IV steroids & antihistamines, and decided to hold off on giving me the third IV antibiotic that was initially planned. I was sent home with Clindamycin 900mg, a Medrol dosepack, and told to discontinue the Bactrim, but continue the Amoxicillin. I continued to check back over the following days, and ended up receiving another IV antibiotic (Clindamycin) and more lab tests. The provider that saw me on Monday said that she was close to admitting me to the hospital, and if I did not improve by the following day, she would proceed with sending me. By the 5th/6th day, the redness seemed to be improving and becoming smaller.
LAB_DATA: Treatment and testing ended up including an ultrasound of the left arm (01/18/21), lab testing (01/18/21, 01/19/21, 01/20/21), multiple IV antibiotics (01/18/21, 01/19/21), IV steroids (01/18/21), IV antihistamines (01/18/21), multiple oral antibiotics (01/16/21, 01/18/21), oral steroids (01/18/21).

Approximately 8 hours after the vaccination I begin to feel itching, burning sensation in my left wrist area surrounding the site of the surgery on Jan. 4 for skin cancer.  This increased over the next few hours and by the next morning my lower forearm was involved.  The surgical site was about 2 inches long, stitches had been removed ten days before and the wound was mostly healed.  The rash extended from the wound site toward the wrist about 2 inches, radiated laterally along the length of the wound about 2 inches on either side and up into the upper forearm another 3 inches.  There were small blisters within the rash as well.  I initially tried a cortisone cream I had left over from a previous wound.  This seemed to inflame the rash even more and I stopped.  I then applied some of the antibiotic cream I used when the wound was fresh and actively treated.  This seemed to reduce the inflammation some.  After 2 days I contacted my dermatologist who prescribed Triamcinolone Acetonide 0.1 % External Cream.  I have been taking this for 24 hours, 3 applications and the rash is beginning to dissipate.  My dermatologist  indicated I was the third patient to have a rash on the same arm with a surgery and a Moderna shot, in the same arm.
LAB_DATA: I sent a picture of the wound site with rash to the doctor.  No other tests were used.
CUR_ILL: I had a skin cancer removed from my left wrist on January 4, stitches removed January 19, wound was healing excellently.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Subjective  57 y.o. male who was seen at COVID Vaccine Clinic today for his second  dose of the COVID 19 vaccination.    He was given the Moderna vaccination in the right deltoid muscle.   During his 15 minute waiting period after the injection, the patient began to experience Right sided chest discomfort, mild shortness of breath and intermittent dizziness.  He denied rash, hives, welts, difficulty breathing, difficulty swallowing, wheezing, throat tightness, hoarseness, stridor, itching, lightheadedness, dizziness, facial swelling, lip swelling and tongue swelling.   This provider was notified of patient reaction and he was then assessed in the emergency  area.   Monitored patient for severe reaction symptoms, including but not limited to abdominal pain, blood pressure abnormality , chest pain, collapse, drooling, hypotension, increased swelling, rapid progression of symptoms, respiratory distress, skin changes, tongue swelling and vomiting. patient denies any previous cardiac history but does have Asthma. Chest discomfort did not worsen with activity and actually improved some per his report. Pulmonary:     Effort: Pulmonary effort is normal. No respiratory distress.     Breath sounds: Normal breath sounds. No wheezing.  Neurological:     Mental Status: He is alert.       Assessment/Plan  Treatment included: albuterol, water and Acetaminophen Follow up response to treatment: Excellent Patient discharge: Stable to go home and follow up with PCP.  Differential Diagnosis: Vaccine-Related Anxiety (include misc mental health) and Local reaction (arm pain, bleeding/bruising, mechanical irritation, localized rash)   Symptoms developed just prior to patient leaving, started visit at 10:05 am, self administered albuterol at 10:10am. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the 1st dose of the Pfizer COVID vaccine on December 17th at 0640. I first started noticing some discoloration on the right side of my neck in a patch on January 1st. Over the course of the next 3 days the area became more red, dry, raised (but still maculopapular), and spread from the right side of my neck around the back of my neck to the left side and then the front. The area was mildly itchy. I had not had any new exposures including no new shampoos, soaps, clothes, sprays, sheets, detergent, etc. I have never had a rash that looked like this, nor have I ever had a rash on my neck. At it's fullest, the rash was a large patch of red, dry skin on my right with small maculopapular circles scattered on the rest of my neck. Around January 6-7th, when I got the second dose, the rash began to spread down my sides. That area was more itchy than my neck. The rash appearance was very consistent, as was the distribution with what I have seen of pityriasis rosea in my patients where you start with a Herald patch somewhere and then the rash spreads to other parts of the body. In January I had sought out an appointment through a virtual healthcare. they were hesitant to start steroids so as not to interfere with my immune response. I started over the counter hydrocortisone. In the few hours after I put it on the rash would be less itchy, less dry appearing and less red, but still noticeably pink, then would return. The rash has finally completely dissipated as of February 3rd morning, so it was present for a little more than a month.
LAB_DATA: I did not receive any medical tests and laboratory results. I had a virtual visit and have pictures that I had shared with my provider.
OTHER_MEDS: Zyrtec, metoprolol, metronidazole topical ointment, Flonase nasal spray
CUR_ILL: No illnesses at time of vaccination or within the month prior.
HISTORY: High blood pressure. Allergic rhinitis. Anxiety. Depression.

Initially she only noted itching in all of the above areas and slight redness of the injection site. She took a single 25 mg dose of diphenhydramine that night and went to bed. The next morning when she woke, her ears were swollen and red, she had blotchy red areas on her face, and increased redness and swelling of the injection site in the right deltoid. She also noted small red "bumps" on her lower legs and thighs bilaterally and across her abdomen as well. She also noted pruritis of her left arm at this time. She took a 10 mg dose of zyrtec this morning around 7:30 AM and then went to an urgent care for evaluation. At the urgent, she was given an IM steroid injection and a prescription for a 5-day course of prednisone 40 mg qday. She has noted significant improvement since receiving the steroid injection earlier today and her symptoms and the skin lesions are nearly completely resolved at this time.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: ED COURSE / MEDICAL DECISION MAKING / TREATMENT PLAN: ED Course and Medical Decision Making: Patient evaluated. Peripheral IV established labs obtained. I do have concern for adverse reaction secondary to the vaccine as her symptoms started she said shortly before an hour after receiving the vaccine is started with tingling in her tongue throat and her body. She has minimal cardiac risk factors. Given she was tachycardic she cannot be perked out. EKG obtained showed no acute ischemic ST elevation or depression. Initial troponin was not elevated. Patient received 500 mL bolus of normal saline she deceived Benadryl and part of Pepcid. While the Benadryl infusion was going on patient reported feeling lightheaded and her heart rate was noted to increase to the 130s briefly. The medications were stopped, the Benadryl had already finished however the Pepcid was not completed. Her heart rate proved quickly and the lightheadedness resolved. Repeat EKG obtained did show some mild ST depression inferiorly. A repeat troponin obtained at 2 hours remain negative D-dimer was elevated to 91 therefore CTA chest was obtained. This showed no evidence of pulmonary embolism there is small groundglass opacity left upper lobe which is likely related to atelectasis do not feel that this is infectious in etiology patient has not had cough fever or chills. She remained on cardiac monitor here without any further tachycardia and her symptoms had resolved. I do believe patient's presentation is secondary to adverse reaction to the vaccination. She was advised to take Benadryl at home and may also try over-the-counter Pepcid at home for her symptoms. Did not feel that steroids were warranted at this time. She is to follow-up closely with her primary care provider. I did advise if she has new or worsening symptoms she should return to the emergency department and she expressed understanding and agreement with this plan.

Spontaneous abortion. Pt was 9w1d at time of first Moderna COVID vaccine (EDD 8/9/2021). Two weeks later she began bleeding and was found to have an incomplete abortion with embryo measuring 9w1d. Proceeded to bleed heavily and D&C performed. Uncomplicated recovery. Genetic studies in process.  Unknown if SAB is related to vaccine, though it appears embryonic demise occurred within a few days of vaccine administration.
LAB_DATA: 1/19/21 - ultrasound confirming embryonic demise 1/20/21 - D&C for incomplete abortion

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt returned to the store after about 55 minutes stating that she was having trouble breathing, her neck felt swollen, and her chest felt heavy.  She also reported feeling shaky.  We called 911 and gave 50 mg of benadryl liquid.  We also checked her blood sugar and found it to be slightly elevated, but not concerning.  By the time the EMTs arrived (5 min or less) she reported already being able to breathe much easier.
Nausea, headache, fever, fatigue.

HISTORY: Brain cancer, allergies, asthma, celiac, hypothyroidism
PRIOR_VAX: Pneumonia shot in 2018

SYMPTOM_TEXT: In discussion with Dr., medical director at Detox, she  arrived night of 2/3/21 was quite intoxicated so was not going through any  withdrawal.  She was getting vitals and CIW  checked regularly.  First dose of  chlordiazepoxide 25mg was 2/4 at 1:25pm for CIWA 9.  She had repeat vitals at  5:50pm, CIWA 1, vitals: P 67, 118/79, 94% on RA, T 98.3.  she had complained of  some "pressure in her head" and feeling anxious, but otherwise denied other  complaints.  she was talking with others in the group, then other patients report  she suddenly started having seizure like activity around 6:45pm, med techs came  to help and found her stiff, gurgling.  they tried to get vitals on her, called  911, noticed that at 6:54pm she had lost a pulse and they started CPR.  paramedics arrived at 7:08pm and she was brought to ED.   Pt BIBA in cardiac arrest. Pt was at Detox Center when she  was reported to have seizure-like activity followed by collapse. She  was found to be pulseless and CPR initiated by staff members. EMS  arrived and performed approx 15 min of CPR and gave pt epi x 3 and  bicarb. No shocks administered but they did not report a rhythm.   In the emergency room the patient arrived and was found to be pulseless with PEA arrest, CPR was initiated, patient was intubated. ROSC ultimately achieved, patient remained very acidotic despite ventilator adjustment, head CT revealed cerebral edema. Pt also found to be profoundly anemic with a hemoglobin of 5 and platelets of 37, she was thought to be GI bleeding so medications for this were initiated. Patient then became more hypoxemic with bradycardia, consultation with neurosurgery and critical care medicine at tertiary care center deemed ongoing CPR futile. Patient arrested at 2:30AM on 2/5, pronounced dead at 2:48AM.

Patient reports about 2 weeks after getting Pfizer COVID vaccine, she started experiencing severe hypoglycemia in the 60s. She was previously on Tresiba 100 units once daily and Novolog 25 units three times daily with meals. She needed to decrease her insulin doses to Tresiba 30 units once daily and Novolog 10 units three times daily with meals and her blood sugars still remained on the low end of normal. She did not have a reaction to the vaccine (i.e. loss of appetite) and no other precipitating factor that would explain such a significant reduction in insulin requirements.

OTHER_MEDS: None taken within 7 days of vaccination

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approximately 12 hours post-injection developed chills (around 10:30 pm). Went to bed and woke up with night sweats, aches, chills, fever (persistently over 100F, topped at 101.3F) and one of the worst headaches I?ve ever had (not hyperbole, truly a monster headache). Slept for small stretches of time, maybe 45-60 mins, before waking. Condition worsened until about 6-7am. Chills persisted but worst symptom was the headache, it was inescapable pain. At 9am, took 400mg ibuprofen and was able to fall asleep.  Woke again around 10:30, soaking wet in sweat, but felt much better. Headache about 95% resolved, fever subsided (temp returned to steady 98.2).  Felt generally tired the rest of the day, but overall much better than the overnight period.
On day 7 a large rash appeared on my arm at the site of the injection site.  Lasted for 5 days.  Red and blustery with a circumference of about 2 1/2 inches.
LAB_DATA: None just maintained vigilance on it.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient had vasovagal syncopal event. This event was not a vaccine side effect but a vasovagal response (previous history of syncope with vaccinations/procedures).   Patient received 1st dose of Pfizer vaccine around 11am today. Within 2 minutes of receiving the vaccine, he started to feel dizzy and passed out for around 45 secs. He had cold extremities, looked pale and was sweating. He was immediately transferred from chair to floor and his legs were raised. Cold towel was placed on his head. He regained consciousness but was confused for less than a 1min. Vitals were checked and his BP was 95/50's and HR was around 56. Pulse O2 was 99% during entire event. He was able to converse well after that and was oriented. He informed having anxiety/panic attacks, had taken his medication that morning. He reported similar syncopal episodes in the past. He was monitored in same posture. He was gently hydrated orally with water and soda. He was given sublingual zofran due to nausea and retching. He did not vomit. We continued to monitor his BP on regular intervals. He had slow improvement in BP and after 2 hrs while sitting his BP was 104/65, pulse 56/min (reports being an athlete and previous records show baseline bradycardia). He denied any symptoms and was awake, alert, oriented.    As he was not accompanied by anyone, his wife was contacted who came to clinic in 10mins and helped to drive him home. He was transported by wheelchair till entrance of clinic. He reported feeling better and thanked for helping.   He does not have any contraindications to receive 2nd dose of vaccine.
HISTORY: GERD Anxiety/Panic attacks Hx of Vasovagal syncope post vaccination

As I came to, I recall really finding relief in the cold tile, and being concerned that I may have hit my head. I did a mental scan of my body and nothing felt painful, though stiff and sore, as I had the flu. I got back in bed and looked at the time, about 20 minutes had elapsed. The rest of the night I tossed turned, and felt quite feverish. I attempted to find radial and carotid pulses, which were extremely weak. That night, I  never did get a temperature, because I was quite disoriented. This morning I?ve been quite stiff and low energy. I feel discomfort in my kidneys, and have taken care to stay hydrated. I have reduced appetite, and some achiness in my body. My temperature right now is 100 even. It?s almost 3 o?clock, so about 28 hours has elapsed. I did not seek further medical care, as I live alone and transportation i would be a hurdle. I also not super concerned, mostly I just want you all to document that I painted, as I have not found that to be listed as a common side effect for the Moderna vaccine. I did call up a friend who is a paramedic, and feel reassured by her two cents.

Difficulty moving arm, arm felt very heavy, so much so that if I was rolling over in bed I couldn't move my arm and needed to use the hand of  my other arm to do so.  Unable to lift arm to the back of my head (for example to put an elastic in my hair) for a week.  A high degree of pain for about 5 days, reducing somewhat after that and lasted about 2 weeks.  Still, nearly 4 weeks later, my arm is sore when I move it at the very top into the shoulder.  It's difficult to hook my bra.  I am not in pain but often have little twinges of pain/discomfort in the upper arm/shoulder, particularly when I lift my arm upward from the side of my body.

I obtained my booster shot on my left deltoid at 2:30 PM 2/4/2021. I had slight soreness in my arm til 8:00 which the soreness disappeared. Around 2:00 AM, I was awakened by a pounding headache, fever of 102, and my upper left chest (unilateral between the midline of my left chest and the axillary region) started to hurt. I took Tylenol 1000 mg at 3 and took a hot bath (recommended by  friend who also displayed a fever and headache). After a while, my fever began to lower but my headache and chest pain did not disappear and I could not sleep until 7 AM. I woke up today (2/5/2021) at 10 AM with a fever of 101.4, another pounding headache, and still unilateral chest pain. I took another 1000 mg of Tylenol around 10:30 AM and it only helped with the fever. I went back to sleep and slept until 4 PM. I understand that the fever and headache are normal symptoms but my chest pain does not seem like muscle soreness. It doesn't hurt when I touch it, it comes and goes every few seconds, I have 4 or 5/ 10 on the pain scale for most of the pain but it turns into 6 or 7/10 occasionally (10 being the worst pain). What does help with my pain when it is 6 or 7/10 is when I clench my chest really hard like I am flexing it. It is a sharp pain that stays for a few seconds before it disappears and it feels like a deep pain. I didn't want to take Tylenol again because I am about to max out (can only take 2 more capsules until 2:00 AM because it states not to take more than 6 capsules in 24 hours, and each capsule is 500 mg) (Also, the Tylenol does not help with the pain so I am only taking it for my fever.) I was wondering if anyone else reported this and if this is an adverse side effect.  This has not cause any issues regarding my breathing but just pain.

Patient arrived to  vaccine clinic for her 1st Pfizer vaccine.  She received her vaccine at 1606.  She was then walked out to the waiting room to wait her 15-20 minutes that is strongly recommended after receiving the vaccine.  Approximately 5 minutes later, she alerted the reception staff that she was having some sort of reaction.  I was then notified immediately and patient was brought back to a private exam area.  Patient complained of chest tightness, numbness in fingers and a racing heartbeat.  She also felt that she was having difficulty breathing.  Vital signs at that time were 96.3 temperature, RR 36, blood pressure 170/100 and a heart rate of 174. 6 minutes after receiving vaccine patient reported that her tongue was starting to swell and that her heart was racing.  Staff called 911 immediately.  Pulse was 166-169, BP 125/88, O2 sat 97%.  No wheezing, and the patient was moving air and talking.  I had an epi-pen on hand but waited since patient was moving air and had such a high HR.  After a few minutes patient reported she felt better and that her tongue was still swollen but not any more so; HR 120s, O2 sat 97%.  EMTs arrived 10:39 a.m., got the same VS, and they decided not to give epinephrine.  Patient was initially reluctant to be transported by ambulance and intended to have sister drive her to ED.  However she reported her tongue was overlapping her teeth all the way around, and was persuaded to go by ambulance.  She walked out of public health clinic into ambulance.  She was treated with IV Benadryl and steroids.  The ED doctor diagnosed anaphylactic reaction but also did not give epinephrine due to tachycardia.  She felt better, but 4 hours afterward she did have a rebound reaction and was treated with more Benadryl and again felt better.  She was discharged from the ED with 2 epi-pens.  She currently feels well.  States that they are having her take PO Benadryl q 4 hours x 48 hours.  She was treated in the emergency department.

Patient received his vaccine and was waiting in the post-vaccination waiting space. Within 5-10 minutes he slumped in his chair and became unresponsive. Became responsive to voice but was slurring his words. Patient was diaphoretic. HR in 90s, O2 98%. His eyes rolled back in his head  suspecting vasovagal episode, we moved patient to the floor  and raised his legs. He became more responsive. Was fully oriented although did not seem incredibly alert. Cycled multiple BPs with 100s-110s/60s-70s. HR 70s-80s  supine, O2 sat 96-98%.  EMS was called for transport to ED given patient's lack of prompt recovery. We  attempted to sit patient up and he again became lightheaded and had to lie back down. While in supine position, remained with normal and stable VS. At no time did he manifest any rash, respiratory symptoms, throat or chest tightness,  abdominal discomfort, or other overt signs of anaphylaxis.   Patient was transported to the ED where ROS was reported as:   - CONST: +fatigue, denies fevers or chills  - EYES: Denies vision changes  - ENT: Denies rhinorrhea, sore throat  - CV: Denies new chest pain  - RESP: Denies SOB or cough  - GI: Denies abd pain, n/v, diarrhea  - GU: Denies dysuria  - MSK: Denies new joint swelling or pain  - SKIN: Denies new lesions or rash  - NEURO: Denies new HA, numbness, or weakness  - PSYCH: Denies suicidal ideation Vitals: BP 116/67, O2 99% on RA, Temp: 97.7F, Pulse 79.  ED provider felt this was most likely vasovagal episode given occurrence following vaccine administration and associated sxs. EKG without evidence of dysrrhythmia. No PE risk factors, SOB or CP. Pt with HA that was not thunderclap nor severe in nature and was consistent with prior migranes, thus do ot suspect SAH. No hx to suggest anemia and no anemia on blood work today. No report of  seizure. Pt is alert without report of post-ictal period.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within a few minutes of vaccine, I got a severe piercing headache and nausea / vomiting which we attributed to nerves and I went to go home without reporting. During the drive the headache and nausea got worse and my extremities and face began to tingle. My chest felt tight. My body was shaking. My colleague noted weak pulses and pale complexion. I am a doctor and gave myself epinephrine 0.3 mg IM and within 60 to 90 seconds the symptoms improved dramatically. I had my husband pick me up at the office and went home. The headache and nausea worsened on the drive but then settled down significantly. I rested for a few hours, then took oral pred 20 mg at about 2:45. I noticed that my headache was back and very intense at about 3:15 pm. No nausea this time, but my left eye began itching and it was very tight / hard to breathe. My extremities began tingling and I had spasms / tremors of my muscles. I injected another 0.3 mg epi into my thigh and followed with dex sodium phosphate 4 mg IM. Symptoms resolved within about 2 to 3 minutes. I took 40mg more of oral pred. I also took 10 mg of pepcid PO.   I am still feeling well now with no headaches or other symptoms at this writing (7:30 pm), but I have another doctor with me and we are 2 minutes from the ER if needed. I am marking unknown below since it has only been a few hours without symptoms.
LAB_DATA: BP remained normal when I was able to check 136 / 62 - this was after the second epi and dex sp.
OTHER_MEDS: Ondansetron 8 mg at 7:30 am Vit D, A, Zinc

The patient stated that he had been fasting for 2 days and we determined low blood sugar likely played into his response to the vaccine.  Glucose gel was placed in mouth and patient felt better within 15 minutes.

Later, I had a telehealth appt with my primary care dr appt - on January 8th. 32 weeks pregnant and second dose of Covid vaccine received on 1/21 at 11:00. Flu like symptoms (fever, chills, headache) began 0100 on 1/22 and lasted until about 1300 on 1/23. I had to call out sick from work on 1/22. Worked a 7L shift on 1/24 and at about 2000 noticed a petechial rash on bilateral lower extremities that spread up to lower abdomen. Called on-call L&D Doctor and she advised for me to be assessed at L&D triage. I was then admitted for 4 hours due to my rash and further workup concerning for DIC, thrombocytopenia and/or other possibilities. My petechial rash was very concerning for coagulation disorders and prompted many lab draws to be obtained. My labs showed elevated AST & ALT that were previously normal, low platelet count (thrombocytopenia), protein in urine, elevated alk phos. I was discharged around 0100 for further workup the following day.  On 1/25 I went to clinic to have more labs done per Doctor. 1/26 at about 0830 I was called by my OB Docotor to immediately go back to Labor & Delivery triage to be admitted for what she thought was preeclampsia based on my labs from 1/25 and 1/24. I was again admitted for about 4 hours for monitoring of baby, and myself for preeclampsia. My labs were still elevated and out of range mirroring preeclampsia, but my blood pressure was stable, so I was discharged around 1300. I followed up with labs at clinic on 1/28 and again on 2/2 as well as with home blood pressure monitoring.  My labs on 2/2 showed everything back to normal, causing the doctors involved in my care to believe this was an adverse event due to the moderna covid vaccine.  As a result I missed one day of work, was admitted to the hospital twice, and had 4 days of lab draws which will result in an excess of medical bills.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1) The right portion of my lower lip started to swell on Tuesday (Feb2) or Wednesday (Feb3); I don?t remember which day. It?s been getting a little worse every day, including today (Friday). I?ve been regularly putting petroleum jelly on my right, lower lip to relieve the discomfort. I?ve also been putting petroleum jelly all over my lower and upper lips, because both lips have become unusually dry since the swelling began.  2A) Part of my skin (near the needle?s point of entry on my arm) came off when I removed band-aid at end of my shower on Tuesday (Feb2) morning.  The narrow, skin-missing area on my arm is a little less than the size in length of the width of the band-aid that I removed. (I have a photo if you?d like to see it.) Although I turned shower water off before removing the band-aid, that raw skinless part of my arm started to sting and burn profusely, immediately after I removed band-aid. The steam (not water) from the shower stall is what burned so badly. When looking in mirror to investigate source of pain, I was puzzled as to why my skin was missing.   2B)Wednesday (Feb3) morning, my husband attempted to put Neosporin on that small portion of my skinless arm to prevent infection from setting in. But it was so painful, I had to stop him. The area burned for more than an hour. So now I keep the band-aid on that spot and don?t remove it. It?s still very sensitive, and I feel discomfort while taking a shower. But since I leave band-aid on, it doesn?t burn and sting like before. And It wasn?t until Thursday (Feb4), after looking online at missing skin, that I realized that my skin apparently came off when I removed the bandage. I also read, when looking online, that skin removal with bandages can happen more often with older folks like myself. I?m not sure if this is an adverse reaction to the vaccine or not but thought I?d report it just in case.

On January 27, 2021 at around noon I received the first dose of the Pfizer/BioNTech Covid-19 vaccine. After approximately 10-15 minutes I noticed a reaction. I was really lightheaded , short of breath, and shaking. It felt like I was going to pass out. I was given water and a bar to eat, and eventually I got to a place where I felt that I could drive. I went for a walk with a couple of friends, but was having a hard time walking because of shortness of breath, and was still lightheaded plus I had skin tingling on both sides of my face. I ate something afterward the walk and felt better within an hour. The next day I seemed to be fine, but then Friday (two days after the shot) I became increasingly lightheaded/dizzy and nauseous. Additionally, I had issues on Friday and Saturday with anxiety and trying to hold off mild panic attacks plus depression and nausea. I was still lightheaded/dizzy and had shortness of breath for a week after the shot. which has extend to today (February 5, 2021), over a week after the shot.

I have had 4 adverse events over the course of the 2 shot series.  I did not realize these represented adverse events until after the 2nd dose.  30 minutes after the 1st shot (this is the one I noted in this report), while driving home from the vaccination center, my face became itchy and hot.  I became panicked, and had a panic attack. I pulled off the road, and dealt with my panic symptoms which were  typical for me when I have panic attacks (sense of doom, extreme fear that I am dying, depersonalization).  I forgot that it was triggered by itching.  In fact, I did not report a reaction to the vaccine center when I got my 2nd shot because I considered it a panic attack, which is not new, and I had forgotten about the itching.  I  remembered this happened when I received the 2nd shot on 2/2/21 at 2:00 and remained at the center for 30 min (due to my sulfa allergy).  Again driving home (abt 45 min  after the vaccine) my face became itchy and hot.  It lasted approximately 20 min, and resolved.  No other acute symptoms .  However, I've developed a mild stomatitis after both shots.  Several days after the first shot I woke up to find extensive sloughing of my buccal mucosa.  .  There was no pain, but I continued to have sloughing  for several  days.  it was extremely noticeable the first 2 days, and tapered off.  I also developed a metallic taste in my mouth (that was the most bothersome part) this was very strong for 3-4 days, and has lessened but not resolved completely.    I did not connect any of this with the vaccine.   Today 3 days after the second shot, I woke with more mucosal sloughing in my mouth.  It is  localized to one particular area nearand seems to be deeper layers because there is some tenderness to the area and a lesion. I have some metallic taste in my mouth but it is mild.
OTHER_MEDS: citalopram, trazodone daily, Nitroglycerin ointment for rectal fissure supplements taken often, and unsure if taken the day of vaccination:  Nordic Naturals Algae 715 mg Omega-3, 365 Brand Vitamin B12 500mcg, 365 Brand Vitamin D3 25 mcg, Vi

I'm not sure this is a result of the Shingrix vaccine, but about one month after my first Shingrix shot, I suddenly developed numbness, tingling and burning in my hands, which then spread to my arms (up to elbow) and my feet (up to my lower calf), and on both sides of my body. I was diagnosed with Idiopathic Peripheral Neuropathy. I told every medical professional I consulted with during this time, that the onset of the neuropathy occurred about one month after my first Shingrix shot. I didn't know I could report it until just now, so I am doing so just in case others have reported a similar issue.
LAB_DATA: Full neurological workup and testing, along with comprehensive blood work to rule out all other options before final diagnosis.

After the vaccine was administered, 5-10 minutes later I began to feel a rapid heart rate. One of the nurses came to check on me, I described to her my symptoms, and she let me know if they get worse to inform her. In the next 5 minutes, my head began to hurt, as well as, some chest pain. She checked on me again, and said to let her know if things got worse. Within the next 5-10 minutes after, I had difficulty swallowing and speaking. I raised my hand, and the nurse came over, then proceeded to get help. They then took my blood pressure and heart rate. My blood pressure was 185/103 and I believe my pulse was 156 bpm. I was still having a hard time swallowing and speaking. They proceeded to get an epi pen and the doctor on site, as well as suggested to send me over the ER/ call 911. The doctor checked my lungs, and they noticed my blood pressure and heart rate was not decreasing to a normal level. I was then put in a wheel chair and transferred to the ER. At the ER, my blood pressure and heart rate was still elevated, as well as difficulty swallowing. The doctor ordered Benadryl via IV, steroids, and the epi pen. After having a reaction to the Benadryl, the epi pen was put on hold. After about 15 minutes, I began to feel better. I was put on IV fluids and observation. I was able to leave the ER around 12 pm 2/05/21. At this time,  7:22 pm, I am feeling better with mild muscle aches, and fatigue.

Narrative: Patient with history advanced vascular dementia, hypertensive cerebrovascular disease and stroke, T2DM. Received her second dose of Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine at approximately 14:00 and was reported to have expired at home at 20:55. Dr. (Medical Director) spoke with patient's son/caregiver 2/4/21. Son reports that patient was in her usual health yesterday morning, deemed well enough by son to travel for vaccination. He reports she had no bothersome symptoms after either first or second vaccinations. Specifically denied rash, wheeze, and difficulty breathing. Son was with patient throughout the day. In the evening, when preparing for bed, he noted she became suddenly unresponsive in a similar fashion as she has done several times in past years. While in all previous such episodes she recovered within minutes, last evening she did not regain consciousness, experiences a brief period of labored breathing, and died. Patient's son called 911 and the patient's body was brought to the medical examiners. The medical examiner declined to proceed with autopsy. Patient's son is not interested in autopsy. Patient's son reports confidence that his mother's underlying hypertensive/diabetic cardiovascular disease is the natural cause of her death. Other Relevant Hx:  Symptoms: & Death Treatment:

Narrative:  See "Other Relevant History" in Section 6 above Other Relevant Hx:  76yo man with a history of for C5 tetraplegia 2/2 cervical stenosis leading to neurogenic bowel/bladder (chronic suprapubic catheter) and chronic respiratory failure with tracheostomy, severe dysphagia s/p G tube placement and multiple aspiration pneumonias, COPD GOLD III, hx MRSA bacteremia (7/2018) and E coli bacteremia (12/2019). Patient transferred from Spinal Cord Injury until to ICU on 1/11/2021 due to worsneing dyspnea, hypoxia (80s) and tachycardia and was found to have acute hypoxic respiratory failure likely 2/2 multifocal pneumonia. CXR findings of "There is interval increase in patchy airspace infiltrates and consolidation in bilateral lungs concerning for pneumonia" Patient was started on vancomycin and pip/tazo on 1/11 and tracheal aspirate cultures were obtained for VAP diagnosis which ultimately grew Serratia liquifaciens and Proteus mirabilis. Infectious Diseases was consulted who recommended a switch to ertapenem therapy for a total 10 day course for VAP. UCx/BCx remained negative. On 1/20, a therapeutic bronchoscopy was completed with cultures growing Stenotrophomonas maltophilia and pan-S Klebsiella pneumoniae. The following day a chest tube was inserted and the course of ertapenem completed but vancomycin was continued. By 1/22, patient developed shock liver with ALT/AST 2135/1579 from normal range the day prior and SCr increased to 1.3 from baseline 0.7/cystatin C of 2.46 up from 1.15. Levofloxacin was added for Stenotrophomonas coverage. By 1/25, patient's clinical status continued to decline and Cardiology was consulted for new onset Afib with RVR. Discussion was documented with patient's family who requested DNR. Patient passed away in the early AM on 1/26. Demise does not appear to be related to COVID-19 vaccination but occurred in recent timeframe.   Symptoms:  ElevatedLiverEnzymes & death, pneumonia, afib

Moderna COVID?19 Vaccine EUA

On January 21 I received my first dose of Moderna vaccine on my left arm. After the vaccine I had a red lump that was hot and a bruise that only lasted 2 days. Everything was fine until the January 28th when I developed a large red lump during the day while at work that was severely itchy and hot. When I got home from work I had a low grade fever. I made an appointment with my primary care for the next day which was Friday the 29th. My doctor told me she believes I had cellulitis. I was given an antibiotic 2x a day for 7 days. She drew a purple circle around the area and told me that if it goes outside the marked area or I feel any new symptoms, to go to the emergency room. Saturday morning on the 30th  i woke up to my entire arm red and hot. I felt like I had a huge sunburn. I couldn?t put my sweatshirt on because it was so hot. The emergency room doctor told me I was fine and to keep taking the antibiotics that were given to me yesterday from my primary care doctor. After the emergency room I went to work and started to feel dizzy and nauseous. My hands became sweaty but the rest of my body was cold. I started having a butterfly feeling in my chest. My Apple Watch alerted me that my heart rate was over 100 bpm. That night before bed I had another low grade fever. On Sunday the 31st I noticed the red area was gone but instead it was a dark purple. I felt okay Sunday besides a rapid pulse. Monday February 1st I woke up out of a dead sleep sweating, butterfly feeling in my chest and dizzy. I tried to take my pulse while laying down but it was so fast I couldn?t keep up with it. I put my Apple Watch on which alerted me immediately that my pulse was 152 bpm. I slowly got up but then I passed out falling off of my bed. I couldn?t get any words out because my heart was beating so fast that I couldn?t breathe. I was sweating horribly and had a hard time walking. Had absolutely no strength in my left hand, my arm was purple/red, cold and numb. My arm felt like someone punched me repeatedly and gave me a dead arm. I called my primary doctors office and they were able to get me in that afternoon. All morning my pulse was spiking and then drastically dropping. About an hour and a half before I went to the doctor everything was fine. I was able to talk but still struggled with breathing while talking. The doctor ordered an EKG which came back clear. My pulse and blood pressure was also fine. The doctor told me she believed all of the symptoms I had were from the medication I take at night (doxazosin-to relax my muscles and help with sleep.) She also told me she believed some of it was my mental health issues taking over. She told me the cellulitis looked fine and sent me home. Later that day I felt exhausted and when I woke up from a nap, I had a fever of 100.5. Took Tylenol and it dropped to 99.5 but wouldn?t go any lower. February 2nd  I woke up to a large red ring outside of the purple marker, numb finger tips and butterfly feeling in my chest. All day I received alerts that my pulse was falling and spiking. I sent my primary doctor an email and she told me she didn?t think it was cellulitis anymore, maybe a hematoma but she wasn?t sure. Since January 28th I still struggle everyday with the butterfly feeling in my chest, blurry vision, low grade temps, alerts of pulse, dizziness and breathing difficulties. My arm is always hot, my finger tips are numb and sometimes the strength in my hand is gone. The top of my arm is always a dark purple with red blotches and other times my entire arm is red and hot. When my pulse is very fast, I have a hard time talking, remembering what I was going to say and focusing. I?ve had multiple coworkers ask me if I?m okay because I?ll randomly stop talking and stare off and then I?m alerted that my pulse has either spiked or dropped drastically after spiking. My pulse is never consistent. It is always ranging from 57-155bpm. I realized at first I may have what they call ?COVID arm? but my symptoms haven?t gotten any better. No answers have been given to me or a diagnosis. The first diagnosis that they thought was cellulitis. Then it was ?in my head and behavioral.? Then it was a hematoma. Now it?s an ?I don?t know.? I have tried Benadryl for the itching, ice packs for the days that I?m swollen, Tylenol for the fevers and pain but I never have any relief.
OTHER_MEDS: Hydroxizine, Seroquil, Doxazosin, Levothyroxine, Omeprozol, Larissia, Effexor, Lamictal

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my shot at 6:53pm. I went to the waiting room and waited until my time was up, I was released from my observation station at 7:11pm. I inspected the rest of my body for any rash called my mom and read over the fact sheet that was given to me at time of shot. As per the directions regarding the risk of an allergic reaction I called my primary care doctor because my face was beginning to swell, and my throat started to feel scratchy. My primary care doctor called me back and advise I go to the ER immediately to be monitored for an allergic reaction.  I arrived in a Hospital just before 9pm and checked in at the ER. By the time the doctor saw me at the ER my face was bright red I had developed a rash all over my chest and back and on the injection site, my lips were swollen and had mild throat swelling. At 1:17 PM, I received the vaccine. Around 1:30 PM I started itching and breaking out in hives. I did not say anything because I thought it was my eczema reacting to my nerves. I went home and felt fine for a while. Around 5:30 PM I told my husband my stomach hurt and I had a slight headache, and I was going to lie down. Around 8:30 PM I woke up. Around 11 PM I was feeling kind of light-headed but did not say anything to my husband because I just thought it was my thoughts. I went to bed. Around 3:45 AM I woke up feeling sick, went to bathroom in master bedroom and dry heaved. I returned to the bed from our bathroom, and told my husband I thought I was going to pass out. I have no recollection of the following events, this is information my husband (Brian) shared with me. He said I then stayed standing on the floor, laid my head over on my pillow, and started breathing heavily, and it became progressively heavier to where he stated I sounded like a "wart hog." He said he jokingly said to me, "Are you mutating," then I collapsed onto our bedroom floor. He said he got up immediately, was saying my name as he was walking to me, and I was not responding. He then got on the floor by me, and was rubbing me and trying to wake me, and it took about a minute before I came to. When I came to I was laying on our floor, keep in mind I feel approximately 5 feet as our bed sits 4 to 4.5 feet in the air, and I am 5'8". I hit my hit on our floor, and when I came to I could barely hear him calling my name as there was a loud rushing noise like water in my head. It took about 2-3 minutes before the ringing was completely gone. I then had cold chills off and on for the next 24 hours with nausea, vomiting, dizziness, and headache. On Tuesday following the initial encounter, I went to the ER due to nausea, vomiting, dizziness, and severe headache on right side of head. The ER doctor diagnosed me after a CT with a closed head injury that occurred at initial encounter, so Thursday around 4 AM.
LAB_DATA: EMS at home on 1/28/2021 around 5 AM. Normal blood pressure, normal blood sugar, normal EKG of heart, and normal O2 after initial encounter, but was ruled an adverse reaction to vaccine by EMT. Adverse event led to ER visit on 2/2/2021 at 9:32 AM. CBC w/ diff; CMP; HCG, Qualitative; Troponin;  CT Cervical spine WO contrast; CT head Wo contrast; EKG 12 lead; diphenhydramine lactated ringers; prochlorperazine (for nausea and headache); sent home at 11 AM on 3/28/2021 with prescription for ondanestrin 4mg for nausea.  I have to follow-up with a neurologist on March 29, 2021 to make sure my brain healed properly from the trauma brain injury from hitting my head upon passing out on 3/28/21 at 4 AM, which was approximately 15 hours after receiving the vaccine.
HISTORY: None known of hormonal imbalance - too much male hormone (will disappear with menopause according to medical practitioner)
PRIOR_VAX: 12 years old' hepatitis B- 3rd dose; passed out 30 minutes after vaccine.
ALLERGIES: sulfa (anaphylactic) hydroxyzine (hives) keflex (pass out) salicylic acid (pass out) possible allergy to allegra D (light-headed)

My doctor gave me a steroid injection and put me on prednisone for 5 days and amoxicillin 500mg, 1 gram twice a day.
